id: pm-pim7
title: "Write-time secret detection advisory: mutation paths flag credential-shaped content before it enters the immutable history stream"
description: ""
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,sdk,security
created_at: "2026-07-07T07:01:25.465Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T07:01:25.465Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exports a documented secret-scan primitive with deterministic default rules and unit-tested detection for GitHub token prefixes, private keys, AWS keys, and high-entropy assignments; all text-bearing CLI+MCP mutation paths consult it honoring secret_guard advise/block/off config; advise emits a single stderr line and never alters exit code or output shape; block returns a structured error with an explicit override flag; scanner failure never blocks a mutation; docs cover configuration and the remediation path for already-recorded content"
parent: pm-qwoy
risk: medium
confidence: high
body: "## Context\nEvery mutating action appends permanently to an item's hash-chained JSONL stream — by design, nothing is silently alterable afterwards. That invariant turns a pasted credential into a permanent artifact: the only remediation is the heavyweight recorded redaction workflow (history-redact), which rewrites and re-anchors the chain. The repo already has credential-shape rules (scripts/check-secrets.mjs, exported scanContent + RULES, hardened in pm-h4zb), but they only guard THIS repository's tracked files in CI. The product itself offers no protection: any agent on any pm workspace can pm create/update/append/notes/comments a live token and only discover the problem after it is chained.\n\n## Proposal\nPromote credential-shape detection to an SDK primitive and run it on the text-bearing mutation write path (create, update, append, close reasons, comments, notes, learnings):\n- SDK: a pure scanContent(text) -> findings primitive with the existing rule set (GitHub token prefixes, private keys, AWS keys, generic high-entropy assignments) as the deterministic default, extension-overridable like other scorer/provider contracts.\n- CLI/MCP: config-controlled mode secret_guard = advise (default; one-line stderr warning naming the rule + offset, mutation proceeds) | block (structured error, mutation refused, --allow-secret override for false positives) | off. Never-block principle: advise mode must add no perceptible latency and never fail the mutation on scanner errors.\n- Error/advisory text points at the redaction workflow for content that already landed.\n\n## Why now\nThe immutable-proof roadmap (portable attestation pm-3z0k, workspace stream pm-klo8, completeness gate pm-9yfo) keeps strengthening permanence guarantees; prevention at the write boundary is the missing complement. At thousands-of-agents scale a single leaked credential in a shared workspace is org-wide exposure."
